Sepp (Josef) Hasslberger - I am German, living in Rome, Italy, entrepreneur in the health area importing US produced nutritional supplements to distribute on the Italian market. Languages: German, English, Italian, Portuguese.

My interests are health (naturally), alternative views in physics and (energy) technology, alternative views in economy and, more recently, the idea of linking people up directly in ubiquitous P2P networks as a way forward in transition to a better way of existence for humanity.

Health website: http://www.newmediaexplorer.org/sepp/

Early articles on physics, technology, economy: http://www.hasslberger.com

Current blog on physics, technology, economy: http://blog.hasslberger.com

Some contributions to the P2P idea in: http://p2pfoundation.ning.com/

Some contributions to the evolving idea of money in: http://openmoney.ning.com/

My idea to establish P2P direct connections is tagged "Peernet". 

An article by Robin Good to explain the concept: [http://www.masternewmedia.org/news/2008/03/19/extending_the_internet_the_peernet.htm Extending The Internet: The Peernet OpenMesh] 


